<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4654988>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 19. Oncopagurus monstrosus (Alcock, 1894). a, shield and cephalic appendages; b, carpus and chela of left cheliped; c, carpus and chela of right cheliped; d, chela of same, lateral; e, same, mesial; f, right 2nd pereopod, lateral, g, dactyl of same, mesial; h, right 3rd pereopod, lateral; i, propodus and dactyl of left 4th pereopod; j, telson. Scales = 1 mm (a), 2 mm (b-e), 1 mm (f-h), 0.5 mm (i,j). (lectotype male [SL 4.2 mm], Bay of Bengal, USNM 156566)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4654988/files/figure.png" .

